lines.text: In the past, I haven't been all that sensitive to your needs. That's because I didn't want you to have any.
It's like living with Noel Coward.
He's the only man I've ever liked. More importantly, he's the only man who ever liked me!
I thought I had grown, that I'd developed grace and style, that it wasn't just the money they liked. Well, thank you for blowing that illusion to hell.
You people think you're so much better because you used to be poor. Well, you're not better! We're better!
